        <bioghist id="ref1">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Described by Robert Gallo as "the most successful vaccinologist in history," American microbiologist Maurice Ralph Hilleman developed over three dozen vaccines in his lifetime. He developed eight of the fourteen vaccines routinely recommended: measles, mumps, hepatitis A, hepatitis B, chickenpox, meningitis, pneumonia and Haemophilus influenzae bacteria and also played a role in the discovery of the cold-producing adenoviruses, the hepatitis viruses, and the cancer-causing virus SV40.</p>
